MALAYSIA DAYBOOK: IOI Tackles Palm Allegations, MAA Denies Deal

-- B y   B a r r y   P o r t e r
-- 
2011-04-06T21:25:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-06/malaysia-daybook-ioi-tackles-palm-allegations-maa-denies-deal.html
IOI Corp.,  Malaysia ’s second-biggest
list  palm oil  producer, said it will work with the Roundtable of
Sustainable Palm Oil to address concerns over land disputes and
alleged illegal deforestation in Sarawak by non-governmental
organizations.  The company was suspended as a certified sustainable
producer of the edible oil by the industry group yesterday,
which gave it 28 days to respond to the allegations.  WHAT TO WATCH:
* Boustead Holdings Bhd. annual meeting and media briefing at 11
a.m. in Kuala Lumpur.
* MAA Holdings Bhd. (MAA MK), the Malaysian insurer denied a
Business Times report it may sell 70 percent of Malaysian
Assurance Alliance Bhd. unit to Zurich Insurance Co. for about
1.2 billion ringgit. It’s still in talks.
* MNRB Holdings Bhd. (MNRB MK) received short-term revolving
credit facility of as much as 120 million ringgit from MIDF
Amanah Investment Bank Bhd.
* Gopeng Bhd. (GOP MK) will pay 5 sen/share final dividend, 5
sen/share gross dividend.  MARKETS:
* Malaysia’s FTSE Bursa Malaysia KLCI Index was little-changed.
* The MSCI Asia Pacific Index dropped 0.1 percent.
* The  Dow Jones Industrial Average  gained 0.3 percent.
* Palm oil June-delivery futures advanced 0.3 percent to 3,376
ringgit a metric ton.  BTV HIGHLIGHTS (KL times):
*7:10am DC Peterson Institute Senior Fellow Jacob Kirkegaard
*8:10am TK Fujitsu Research Institute Martin Schultz
*9:40am SY Rabobank Agricultural Analyst Wayne Gordon
*10:10am HK MSI Global President Michael Ivanovitch  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
